-- Nestle Names Brown CEO of North America Water Effective Feb. 1
-- B y   R a c h e l   L a y n e
-- 2012-11-15T20:23:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-15/nestle-names-brown-ceo-of-north-america-water-effective-feb-1.html
Nestle SA (NESN) , the world’s largest food
company, named  Tim Brown  to head its North America water unit
effective Feb. 1 as Kim Jeffery, 64, assumes a non-executive
chairman role after 20 years in the post.  Brown, 49, previously served as president and chief
executive of Nestle Canada, the company said today in a
statement.  North America helped lead sales growth in Nestle’s bottled
water division in the first nine months of the year. The
company’s bottled water brands include Perrier, Poland Springs,
Ice Mountain, S. Pellegrino and Aqua Panna.  The North America division is based in Stamford,
Connecticut, and the parent company is based in Vevey,
Switzerland.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rachel Layne in Boston at 
